{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0118FTBggLp4JvT77dYBjSPm","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Version Reporting Implementation Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the version reporting implementation across all three Cloche binaries. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n### 1. Version Source\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/version/VERSION`\n- **Current Version:** `0.1.0`\n- **Format:** Plain text file with version string\n- **Implementation:** Uses Go's `//go:embed` directive to embed the VERSION file at compile time\n\n**Version Module:** `/workspace/internal/version/version.go`\n```go\nfunc Version() string {\n    return strings.TrimSpace(rawVersion)\n}\n```\n- Returns the embedded version string with trailing whitespace trimmed\n- Single responsibility: always returns the canonical version shared across all binaries\n\n---\n\n### 2. CLI Binary (`cloche`)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n**Flag Handling:**\n- Flags: `-v` and `--version`\n- Location: Lines 33-37 (checked first, before any other commands)\n- Implementation: `cmdVersion()` function (lines 672-719)\n\n**Output Format:**\n```\ncloche <version>\ncloched <version>\ncloche-agent <version>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. Prints CLI version from `version.Version()`\n2. Attempts to fetch daemon version via gRPC `GetVersion()` RPC (3-second timeout)\n   - Falls back to `<unavailable>` if daemon not running or unreachable\n3. Attempts to fetch agent version by running:\n   ```bash\n   docker run --rm --entrypoint cloche-agent <image> -v\n   ```\n   - Image defaults to `cloche-agent:latest` or `CLOCHE_IMAGE` env var\n   - Strips the \"cloche-agent \" prefix from output\n   - Falls back to `<unavailable>` on error\n4. **Version Mismatch Warnings** (stderr):\n   - Warns if daemon version differs from CLI version\n   - Warns if agent version differs from CLI version\n\n**gRPC Call Details:**\n- Client: `pb.NewClocheServiceClient(conn)`\n- Method: `client.GetVersion(ctx, &pb.GetVersionRequest{})`\n- Timeout: 3 seconds\n- Response: `resp.Version`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Daemon Binary (`cloched`)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n**Flag Handling:**\n- Flags: `-v` and `--version`\n- Location: Lines 29-32 (checked first in main())\n- Implementation: Direct output, no function call\n\n**Output Format:**\n```\ncloched <version>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Simple, synchronous output\n- Prints version and exits immediately\n- No network calls or version discovery\n\n---\n\n### 4. Agent Binary (`cloche-agent`)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n\n**Flag Handling:**\n- Flags: `-v` and `--version`\n- Location: Lines 15-18 (checked first in main())\n- Implementation: Direct output, no function call\n\n**Output Format:**\n```\ncloche-agent <version>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Simple, synchronous output\n- Prints version and exits immediately\n- No dependencies on daemon or other services\n\n---\n\n### 5. gRPC Protocol\n\n**Proto Definition:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n**Service Definition (lines 21):**\n```protobuf\nrpc GetVersion(GetVersionRequest) returns (GetVersionResponse);\n```\n\n**Message Definitions (lines 150-154):**\n```protobuf\nmessage GetVersionRequest {}\n\nmessage GetVersionResponse {\n  string version = 1;\n}\n```\n\n**Generated Code:** \n- Client method: `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go` (line 169)\n  ```go\n  func (c *clocheServiceClient) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, in *GetVersionRequest, opts ...grpc.CallOption) (*GetVersionResponse, error)\n  ```\n- Server implementation: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 1135-1137)\n  ```go\n  func (s *ClocheServer) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetVersionRequest) (*pb.GetVersionResponse, error) {\n      return &pb.GetVersionResponse{Version: version.Version()}, nil\n  }\n  ```\n- Full method name: `/cloche.v1.ClocheService/GetVersion`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Version Module Tests\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/version/version_test.go`\n\n**Tests:**\n1. `TestVersion()`: Verifies version string is not empty and equals \"0.1.0\"\n2. `TestVersionNoTrailingNewline()`: Verifies trailing whitespace is properly stripped\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Binary | Flags | Entry Point | Output Format | Dependencies |\n|--------|-------|-------------|--------------|--------------|\n| `cloche` | `-v, --version` | cmdVersion() | 3-line multi-version output | gRPC daemon, Docker |\n| `cloched` | `-v, --version` | main() direct | Single-line daemon version | None |\n| `cloche-agent` | `-v, --version` | main() direct | Single-line agent version | None |\n\n### Key Design Points\n\n1. **All three binaries share the same version file** (`internal/version/VERSION`)\n2. **CLI performs cross-service version discovery**, warning on mismatches\n3. **Daemon and Agent are simple and stateless** regarding version reporting\n4. **gRPC endpoint enables programmatic version checking** independent of daemon command-line\n5. **Embedded VERSION file** ensures version is baked into each binary at compile time\n6. **3-second timeout** on gRPC calls prevents CLI hang if daemon is unresponsive"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa2ae32e1519e37cb (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54274\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 23830</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5888bf68-422b-4315-97ee-07c9cf3aacfd","uuid":"edd995cb-e045-4e36-9158-1248c7f86769","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the version reporting implementation in this codebase. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read internal/version/ directory - all files\n2. Read cmd/cloche/main.go - how does the CLI handle -v/--version?\n3. Read cmd/cloched/main.go - how does the daemon handle -v/--version?\n4. Read cmd/cloche-agent/main.go - how does the agent handle -v/--version?\n5. Read internal/adapters/grpc/server.go - the GetVersion gRPC endpoint\n6. Read api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto - the proto definition for version\n7. Read api/clochepb/ files for generated code\n\nReport back the exact flags, function names, output formats, and behavior for version reporting across all three binaries.","agentId":"aa2ae32e1519e37cb","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Version Reporting Implementation Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the version reporting implementation across all three Cloche binaries. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n### 1. Version Source\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/version/VERSION`\n- **Current Version:** `0.1.0`\n- **Format:** Plain text file with version string\n- **Implementation:** Uses Go's `//go:embed` directive to embed the VERSION file at compile time\n\n**Version Module:** `/workspace/internal/version/version.go`\n```go\nfunc Version() string {\n    return strings.TrimSpace(rawVersion)\n}\n```\n- Returns the embedded version string with trailing whitespace trimmed\n- Single responsibility: always returns the canonical version shared across all binaries\n\n---\n\n### 2. CLI Binary (`cloche`)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n**Flag Handling:**\n- Flags: `-v` and `--version`\n- Location: Lines 33-37 (checked first, before any other commands)\n- Implementation: `cmdVersion()` function (lines 672-719)\n\n**Output Format:**\n```\ncloche <version>\ncloched <version>\ncloche-agent <version>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. Prints CLI version from `version.Version()`\n2. Attempts to fetch daemon version via gRPC `GetVersion()` RPC (3-second timeout)\n   - Falls back to `<unavailable>` if daemon not running or unreachable\n3. Attempts to fetch agent version by running:\n   ```bash\n   docker run --rm --entrypoint cloche-agent <image> -v\n   ```\n   - Image defaults to `cloche-agent:latest` or `CLOCHE_IMAGE` env var\n   - Strips the \"cloche-agent \" prefix from output\n   - Falls back to `<unavailable>` on error\n4. **Version Mismatch Warnings** (stderr):\n   - Warns if daemon version differs from CLI version\n   - Warns if agent version differs from CLI version\n\n**gRPC Call Details:**\n- Client: `pb.NewClocheServiceClient(conn)`\n- Method: `client.GetVersion(ctx, &pb.GetVersionRequest{})`\n- Timeout: 3 seconds\n- Response: `resp.Version`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Daemon Binary (`cloched`)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n**Flag Handling:**\n- Flags: `-v` and `--version`\n- Location: Lines 29-32 (checked first in main())\n- Implementation: Direct output, no function call\n\n**Output Format:**\n```\ncloched <version>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Simple, synchronous output\n- Prints version and exits immediately\n- No network calls or version discovery\n\n---\n\n### 4. Agent Binary (`cloche-agent`)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n\n**Flag Handling:**\n- Flags: `-v` and `--version`\n- Location: Lines 15-18 (checked first in main())\n- Implementation: Direct output, no function call\n\n**Output Format:**\n```\ncloche-agent <version>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Simple, synchronous output\n- Prints version and exits immediately\n- No dependencies on daemon or other services\n\n---\n\n### 5. gRPC Protocol\n\n**Proto Definition:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n**Service Definition (lines 21):**\n```protobuf\nrpc GetVersion(GetVersionRequest) returns (GetVersionResponse);\n```\n\n**Message Definitions (lines 150-154):**\n```protobuf\nmessage GetVersionRequest {}\n\nmessage GetVersionResponse {\n  string version = 1;\n}\n```\n\n**Generated Code:** \n- Client method: `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go` (line 169)\n  ```go\n  func (c *clocheServiceClient) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, in *GetVersionRequest, opts ...grpc.CallOption) (*GetVersionResponse, error)\n  ```\n- Server implementation: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 1135-1137)\n  ```go\n  func (s *ClocheServer) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetVersionRequest) (*pb.GetVersionResponse, error) {\n      return &pb.GetVersionResponse{Version: version.Version()}, nil\n  }\n  ```\n- Full method name: `/cloche.v1.ClocheService/GetVersion`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Version Module Tests\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/version/version_test.go`\n\n**Tests:**\n1. `TestVersion()`: Verifies version string is not empty and equals \"0.1.0\"\n2. `TestVersionNoTrailingNewline()`: Verifies trailing whitespace is properly stripped\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Binary | Flags | Entry Point | Output Format | Dependencies |\n|--------|-------|-------------|--------------|--------------|\n| `cloche` | `-v, --version` | cmdVersion() | 3-line multi-version output | gRPC daemon, Docker |\n| `cloched` | `-v, --version` | main() direct | Single-line daemon version | None |\n| `cloche-agent` | `-v, --version` | main() direct | Single-line agent version | None |\n\n### Key Design Points\n\n1. **All three binaries share the same version file** (`internal/version/VERSION`)\n2. **CLI performs cross-service version discovery**, warning on mismatches\n3. **Daemon and Agent are simple and stateless** regarding version reporting\n4. **gRPC endpoint enables programmatic version checking** independent of daemon command-line\n5. **Embedded VERSION file** ensures version is baked into each binary at compile time\n6. **3-second timeout** on gRPC calls prevents CLI hang if daemon is unresponsive"}],"totalDurationMs":23830,"totalTokens":54274,"totalToolUseCount":14,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":791,"cache_read_input_tokens":52043,"output_tokens":1436,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":791},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
