ing, manages Docker containers, records captures, exposes gRPC API\n  - `cloche-agent` (In-Container): autonomous, parses DSL, executes steps, streams status\n- **Communication protocols:**\n  - CLI ↔ Daemon: gRPC with protobuf contracts\n  - Agent ↔ Daemon: structured JSON over stdout\n- **Workflow DSL vocabulary** (workflow, step, result, wiring, done, abort)\n- **Hexagonal architecture** (ports and adapters)\n- **Container model** (one container per run, git-based file extraction)\n- **Capture system** (step inputs/outputs/results recorded)\n- **Security boundaries** (filesystem, network, environment isolation)\n\n#### 4. **docs/workflows.md** (`/workspace/docs/workflows.md`)\nComplete workflow DSL reference with:\n- **Workflow locations:**\n  - Container workflows (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) — run in Docker\n  - Host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`) — run on host machine\n  - Three workflow phases: `list-tasks`, `main`, `finalize`\n- **Step types:** `agent` (prompt), `script` (run), `workflow` (dispatch container workflow, host only)\n- **DSL syntax** (workflow declaration, step config, wiring, results)\n- **Wire output mappings** (extract values from step output, inject as env vars)\n- **Key properties** (type inference, result declaration, separate wiring, parse-time validation)\n- **Execution model** (container vs host, environment variables)\n- **`list-tasks` output format** (JSONL with id, status, title, description, metadata)\n- **Host workflow example** (three-phase orchestration)\n\n#### 5. **docs/USAGE.md** (`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`)\nComplete CLI usage guide with:\n- **Core concepts** (workflow, step, result, wiring, terminals)\n- **Workflow DSL detailed reference** (step configuration, container blocks, host blocks, wiring syntax)\n- **Step configuration keys:**\n  - `prompt`, `run`, `workflow_name`\n  - `results`, `max_attempts`, `timeout`\n  - `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `feedback`, `prompt_step`\n- **Result protocol** (`CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker format)\n- **Prompt assembly** (step template, user request, validation output, result selection)\n- **Agent command resolution** (priority order, fallback chains)\n- **Workflow locations** (container vs host)\n- **Host step environment variables:**\n  - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`\n  - `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME`, `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID`\n- **Container environment variables:**\n  - `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`\n- **Complete CLI commands reference:**\n  - `cloche init` — scaffold new project\n  - `cloche run` — launch workflow run\n  - `cloche status` — check run status\n  - `cloche list` — list runs\n  - `cloche logs` — stream logs\n  - `cloche poll` — block until completion\n  - `cloche stop` — cancel run\n  - `cloche delete` — delete container\n  - `cloche health` — per-project summary\n  - `cloche workflow` — list/render workflows\n  - `cloche project` — project info\n  - `cloche get/set` — run context store\n  - `cloche tasks` — task pipeline\n  - `cloche loop` — orchestration loop\n  - `cloche shutdown` — shutdown daemon\n- **Project layout** (`.cloche/` directory structure)\n- **Daemon configuration:**\n  - `CLOCHE_LISTEN` (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n  - `CLOCHE_DB` (default: `cloche.db`)\n  - `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` (default: `docker`)\n  - `CLOCHE_IMAGE` (default: `cloche-agent:latest`)\n  - `CLOCHE_HTTP` (web dashboard address)\n  - `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH`, `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND`\n  - `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS`, `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n- **Client configuration:**\n  - `CLOCHE_ADDR`, `CLOCHE_HTTP`\n- **Dockerfile requirements** (cloche-agent, git, agent user, /workspace directory)\n- **Build commands** (make build, test, lint, proto, docker-build, install)\n\n#### 6. **docs/INSTALL.md** (`/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`)\nInstallation guide with:\n- Prerequisites (Docker, Git, Go 1.25+)\n- Build from source (`make install`)\n- `go instal